<p>I was fishing an Alexandra (shown below) because it is a beautiful fly and has a history. It was invented in 1860 and originally called the ‚ÄúLady of the Lake‚Äù. It was later renamed in honour of Princess Alexandra of Denmark who married Edward VII in 1863. In the old days, it was so effective that there was talk of banning this fly.<figure class="">
  &lt;a href=</figure></p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>  "/assets/images/2013/01/P1050458.jpg"
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>&lt;img src=</p>

